    public class Action3ToAction3Async<T1,​T2,​T3>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Action3Async<T1,​T2,​T3>
    An adapter that converts a conventional Action3 to an Action3Async. All asynchronous calls are executed in another thread and forwarded to the Action3.accept(Object, Object, Object) method. The Executor to use for the asynchronous invocations can be chosen during creation of this adapter. If no explicit executor is given the a default executor is used. The default executor can be set using the AsyncExecutor.setDefaultExecutor(Executor) property or is created automatically by the AsyncExecutor.
    Author:
    tilmann

        public ActionAsyncResult beginAccept​(java.util.function.Consumer<ActionAsyncResult> callback,
                                     java.lang.Object asyncState,
                                     T1 parameter1,

                                     T3 parameter3)
        Asynchronously invoke this Action3Async with the given parameter value, callback and asyncState.

        Associated with each call to beginInvoke is an ActionAsyncResult instance returned by the call and given to the callback that can be used to track the status and outcome of the invocation.

        Specified by:
        beginAccept in interface Action3Async<T1,​T2,​T3>
        Parameters:
        callback - the Consumer, if given to beginInvoke, is invoked upon completion of the Action3Async's invocation and receives the same ActionAsyncResult that is returned by the call to beginInvoke.
        asyncState - the asyncState is an arbitrary reference that, if given to beginInvoke, can be retrieved from this invocations ActionAsyncResult.getAsyncState()
        parameter1 - the first parameter's value for the invocation
        parameter2 - the second parameter's value for the invocation
        parameter3 - the third parameter's value for the invocation
        Returns:
        the ActionAsyncResult associated with this asynchronous invocation
